          <a href="http://blog.batchblue.com"><h2 id="h2-blog"><span class="hidetext">BatchBook Blog</span></h2></a>

				
<div id="post-65" class="post">

          <h1><a href="http://blog.batchblue.com/more-virtual-tools-second-life-as-collaboration-space/" title="Permanent Link to More Virtual Tools: Second Life as collaboration space">More Virtual Tools: Second Life as collaboration space</a></h1>

          <div class="postmetadata">
          <img src="http://batchblue.com/images/4-thumb.jpg" alt="Pamela O'Hara" />
            <ul>
              <li class="postdate">Posted March 3rd, 2008</li>
              <li class="author">By <a href="http://blog.batchblue.com/?author=4" title="Archive for Pamela O'Hara">Pamela O'Hara</a> (<a href="http://batchblue.com/pamela-ohara.html">bio</a>)</li>
              <li class="categories">Filed under: <a href="http://blog.batchblue.com/category/how-we-do-it/" title="View all posts in How We Do It" rel="category tag">How We Do It</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div> <!-- close .postmetadata -->

<p><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="355" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="wmode" value="transparent" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/MN-pMZxEQzA" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="355" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/MN-pMZxEQzA" wmode="transparent"></embed></object></p>
<p>In the effort to continually update the <a href="http://www.batchblue.com/bluepaper-virtualoffice.html">Running a Virtual Office Blue Paper</a>, I sat down for a few minutes at the recent <a href="http://secondlife.com/">NewBCamp</a> event with <a href="http://www.3greeneggs.com/wp/">Hilary Mason</a>, a computer science professor at Johnson and Wales Univeristy.  She talks about using <a href="http://secondlife.com/">Second Life </a>as a virtual collaboration tool.  This is intriguing.  I think we&#8217;ll have to follow up with her and get a demo of the tools available and how they better the collaboration experience.</p>
<div style="padding-top:5px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:5px;padding-left:0px;;">
